node.text:
This spectacular 1.6 acre property rests high above the glistening waters of the Long Island Sound and Larchmont Harbor, with over 500 ft of private shoreline, a deep water dock, a jetty, and an area for swimming or launching a small watercraft. Magnificently sited on a lush promontory adjacent to Manor Park, this beautiful 8,182 SF, 1898 Victorian is designed to highlight the gorgeous panoramas from every room. Experience unobstructed views from the wraparound porch, bluestone patio, in-ground pool & spa. An original stable is now a 3 bed, 2 bath guest house with chic-retro kitchen. At the heart of this 3-level turreted icon is a great room that soars 2 stories with stairway to a glass cupola. Each space melds period grandeur with glamour. This home is unrivaled.
25 Park Avenue, Larchmont, NY $11,300,000
7 Bedrooms
6/2 Baths
Don’t miss out on the opportunity to own this extraordinary waterfront home, listed with @Mimi.Magarelli. Learn more via the link below.
https://wpsir.co/25ParkAvenue

Designed by the architectural firm Gray Organschi in collaboration with an intentional owner - Il Poggio delivers on a vision that many desire, but only a few will accomplish.
As you enter the property from a quiet country road, a modernist form emerges as if rising from the hillside. Inch closer to the portico entrance and the promise of serene relaxation, active endeavors, intimate gatherings, and memorable events unfolds. With walls of glass enhanced by the natural beauty of wood and stone, unobstructed views of the lush landscape come into view from every room. Swim or paddle a canoe on the crystal clear pond, play tennis on the lighted courts, or tinker in the hobby barn. Stroll to the edge of the hillside and find “the folly” reminiscent of a Roman amphitheater where family and renowned musicians have performed. Don't miss out on this private enclave unlike any other offered in the Litchfield Hills.
46c Senff Road, Washington, CT $11,950,000
5 Bedrooms
7/4 Baths
Don't miss out on the opportunity to own this stunning home, listed

Welcome home to this beautiful shingle-style house.
This custom-built home is located in sought-after Vineyard Point, Sachems Head, Guilford, CT. Boasting direct waterfront living, this home was designed by architect Tony Terry with gorgeous unobstructed views of Long Island Sound, Faulkner's Island, and views of approx 10 acres of lush protected tidal salt marsh to the rear of the property. Enjoy swimming from the 100' private beach and rocks. The wonderful wrap around porch affords endless hours of relaxing in the fresh air and enjoying expansive water views and active wildlife. The first floor boasts an open floor plan, perfect for everyday living and entertaining. Boasting views from every window, this home is a must-see.

Welcome to this historic Westport home.
Once, in Old Westport, there was a charming boat club on the Sherwood Mill Pond. It was sited on a 1.9 acre point with 180’ of breathtaking unobstructed water views. Over time, with care and architectural integrity, the property has evolved into a well loved and tended home with gracious spaces, style, comfort and unequaled water views. Extensively enlarged and remodeled in 1989, and true to tradition the original clubhouse is the one you want to come home to. Enter through the roses and rhododendrons on the flagstone path to the gracious front entry foyer into the jaw dropping great room, anchored by the original stone fireplace with views of the pond along an entire window wall. On a summer day, after tennis on the court, walk the path to the pool, or canoe on the pond. The privacy is enviable, the home, gracious and warm, the views breathtaking.
 
 30 Edgewater Hillside, Westport, CT $5,900,000
6 Bedrooms
4/2 Baths
Don’t miss out on the opportunity to own this stunning waterfront property, listed with Karen Curtis. Learn more via the link in bio.
